tanglement between honorific practices and the religious life at that time. Reconsidering the relationships between honours and religion, also implies reversing the question of the influence of Greek religion on Hellenistic ruler cults.This perspective allows us to explore how a new tradition of ritual encounters between human power and the divine sphere may have impacted post-classical developments in Greek polytheism."--Page 4 of cover. 0aGreecexKings and rulersxReligious aspects. 0aReligion and politicszGreece. 0aDivine right of kingsxHistory. 0aWorshipxHistory. 0aGods, GreekxNames. 0aEpiclesis.2 aCentre international d'âetude de la religion grecque antique,eissuing body. 0aKernos.pSupplâement ;v41.8 hReCAP 23-112883  aAUXAM  aRL  aCAN-AP AUG 2023 1z8528aReCAP 23-112883i33433135521577p34.87vAUXAM  s3948tMALu41901apprv  a230919b3487c461e3948f39000845g104738cam  2200445 i AAL08292435-0001Fr-PaAMA20230914073728.0230803t20232023be ah    b    101 0 eng d  a9782503605586q(hardback)c95,00 EUR  a(OCoLC)1371246167  aFr-PaAMAbengerda 4aBX4662b.I57 202314a235a27000aInteracting with saints in the late Antique and Medieval worlds /cedited by Robert Wisniewski, Raymond Van Dam and Bryan Ward-Perkins. 1aTurnhout, Belgium :bBrepols,c[2023] 4cÃ2023  a282 pages :billustrations (chiefly color), facsimiles ;c24 cm.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier1 aHagiologia-âetudes sur la saintetâe et l'hagiographie =aStudies on sanctity and hagiography,x1378-1006 ;vvol. 20  aBased on a colloquium held at University of Warsaw, Warsaw, Poland, 2018.  aIncludes bibliographical references and index.00t Abbreviations -- t Robert Wisniewski, Introduction -- t Seeing and Hearing the Saints -- t Robin M. Jensen, Icons as Relies, Relies as Icons -- t Maria Lidova, Placing Martyrs in the Apse : Visual Stratâegies for the Promotion of Saints in Late Antiquity -- t Julia Doroszewska, Saintly In-betweeners : The Liminal Identity of Thekla and Artemios in their Lare Antique Miracle Collections -- t Arkadiy Avdokhin, Resounding Martyrs : Hymns and the Veneration of Saints in Lare Antique Miracle Collections -- t Les saints myroblytes en Orient et en Occident jusqu'áa l'an mil : Prolâegomáenes áa l'histoire d'un phâenomáene miraculeux -- t Local and Cosmopolitan Cuits -- t Andrãas Handl, Reinvented by Julius, Ignored by Damasus : Dynamics of the Cult of Callixtus in Lare Antique Rome -- t Stephanos Efthymiadis, The Cult of Saints in Constantinople (Sixth-Twelfth Century) : Some Observations -- t Anna Lampadaridi, The Origins and Later Development of the First Italo-Greek Hagiographies : The Dossiers of the Sicilian Martyrs Agatha, Lucia, and Euplus -- t Constructing Paradigms -- t Ian Wood, The Lives of Episcopal Saints in Gaul : Models for a Time of Crisis, c. 470-550 -- t Michal Pietranik, Saints and Sacred Objeccs in Eastern Roman Imperia Warfare : The Case of Maurice (582.-602) -- t Nikoloz A Leksidze, Martyrs, Hunters and Kings : The 'Political Theologi of Saints' Relies in Late Antique Caucasia -- t Index of Saints, Persons, Places, and Subjects.  a "The cuit of saints is one of the mort fascinating religious developments of Late Antiquity and the early Middle Ages. Christians admired martyrs already in the second century, but for a long time they perceived them only as examples to follow and believed they could pray directly to God, whom they addressed as 'Our Father'. A new attitude toward saints, now considered above ail as powerful friends of God and efficient intercessors, began to emerge in the third century. Once this process gained momentum in the Constantinian era, the cuit of saints constantly changed and rapidly adapted to new conditions and demands. This evolution highlighted many factors : the popularity of specific saints and the different types of sanctity, the spread of cuits and customs, and the ways in which the saints were described, visualised, and represented. This volume seeks to capture the dynamic of these adaptations, showing both those aspects of cuit which evolved quickly and those which remained stable for long periods of time. It studies the evolution of the cuits over a broad period from the third to the seventh centuries and in various regions from Gaul to Georgia, with a particular interest in the two greatest centres of the cuit of saints : Rome and Constantinople. In response to changing needs and different circumstances, new generations of believers repeatedly modified the cuits of established saints, even as they introduced new saints."--Page 4 of cover. 0aChristian saintsxCultxHistory of doctrinesyEarly church, ca. 30-600vCongresses. 0aChristian saintsxCultxHistory of doctrinesyMiddle Ages, 600-1500vCongresses.1 aWisniewski, Robert,d1968-eeditor.1 aVan Dam, Raymond,eeditor.1 aWard-Perkins, Bryan,eeditor.2 aUniwersytet Warszawski,ehost institution. 0aHagiologia ;vvol. 20.8 hReCAP 23-112888  aAUXAM  aRL  aWIS-AP AUG 2023 1z8528aReCAP 23-112888i33433135521833p125.54vAUXAM  s13015tMALu50145RCR  a230919b12554c461e13015f39000845g103818cam  2200397 i AAL08201665-0001Fr-PaAMA20230904144057.0221007m20229999fr adh   b    000 0 fre d  a9782368020180q(paperback ;qv. 1)c20,00 EUR  a(OCoLC)1373372045  aFr-PaAMAbengerda 4aGV943.9.P65bL44 202214a7961 aLegat, Frâedâerik,eauthor.10aGâeopolitique du football /cFrâedâerik Legat. 1aParis :bBibliomonde âeditions,c[2022]- 4cÃ2022-  avolumes :billustrations, charts, facsimiles ;c21 cm  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier  aIncludes bibliographical references.1 a[1]. 1900-191400t Prâeface de Pascal Boniface -- t La situation en 1914 -- t La Premiáere Guerre mondiale -- t Une reprise progressive dans un monde nouveau -- t La montâee en puissance des nouveaux pays d